.container
  %ul.cards
    %li.cards__item
      .card
        .card__image.card__image--fence
        .card__content
          .card__title Flex
          %p.card__text This is the shorthand for flex-grow, flex-shrink and flex-basis combined. The second and third parameters (flex-shrink and flex-basis) are optional. Default is 0 1 auto.
          %button.btn.btn--block.card__btn Button
    %li.cards__item
      .card
        .card__image.card__image--river
        .card__content
          .card__title Flex Grow
          %p.card__text This defines the ability for a flex item to grow if necessary. It accepts a unitless value that serves as a proportion. It dictates what amount of the available space inside the flex container the item should take up.
          %button.btn.btn--block.card__btn Button
    %li.cards__item
      .card
        .card__image.card__image--record
        .card__content
          .card__title Flex Shrink
          %p.card__text This defines the ability for a flex item to shrink if necessary. Negative numbers are invalid.
          %button.btn.btn--block.card__btn Button
    %li.cards__item
      .card
        .card__image.card__image--flowers
        .card__content
          .card__title Flex Basis
          %p.card__text This defines the default size of an element before the remaining space is distributed. It can be a length (e.g. 20%, 5rem, etc.) or a keyword. The auto keyword means "look at my width or height property."
          %button.btn.btn--block.card__btn Buttonp